      "parents": [
        {
          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/commits/f50d53c84736f8ada8419346c4d1734d5a6686d4",
          "sha": "f50d53c84736f8ada8419346c4d1734d5a6686d4",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/f50d53c84736f8ada8419346c4d1734d5a6686d4"
        }
      ],
      "message": "mining: add submitBlock IPC method to Mining interface\n\nAdd a submitBlock method to the Mining IPC interface, similar to the\nsubmitblock RPC. This accepts a fully assembled block, validates it, and\nif accepted as new, processes it into chainstate.\n\nUnlike the submitblock RPC, this method does NOT auto-add the coinbase\nwitness nonce (via UpdateUncommittedBlockStructures). Since this is a new\ninterface and SegWit has been active for years, callers must provide a\nfully-formed block including the coinbase witness nonce when a witness\ncommitment is present.\n\nThis is needed for Stratum v2 Job Declarator Server (JDS), where accepted\nsolutions may correspond to jobs not tied to a Bitcoin Core BlockTemplate.\nJDS receives PushSolution fields and reconstructs full blocks; without an\nIPC submitBlock method, final submission requires the submitblock RPC.\n\nThe method returns detailed status (reason/debug strings) matching the\ncheckBlock pattern, giving callers enough information to handle\nvalidation failures.",
      "committer": {
        "name": "w0xlt",
        "email": "94266259+w0xlt@users.noreply.github.com",
        "date": "2026-02-24T21:16:34Z"
      },
      "author": {
        "name": "woltx",
        "email": "94266259+w0xlt@users.noreply.github.com",
        "date": "2026-02-20T23:30:09Z"
      },
      "sha": "62274040599b3a21eec39ee6f7c84da7e3fb2762"
    },
